Each point represents the biomass ratio at the start of the year and the relative fishing intensity in that same year. Lines through the final point show 95% intervals based on the asymptotic uncertainty for each dimension. The shaded ellipse is a 95% region which accounts for the estimated correlation between the two quantities: -0.84. The vertical line at 0.4 indicates the reference point as defined in the forecast.ss which can be removed from the plot via SS_plots(..., btarg = -1).
